Jeff Wicks, News24Johannesburg - South Africa&rsquo;s top matriculant said his achievements were the result of consistent hard work over several years. Conrad Strydom, of Hermanus High School in the Western Cape, was announced as the country&rsquo;s top achiever by Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga in Midrand on Wednesday night.Get your Matric Results online tomorrow at 06:00 hereHe planned to study theoretical physics at Stellenbosch University. &ldquo;I am really honoured to have achieved these awards and feel really proud and excited,&rdquo; he said.&ldquo;In my case it was hard work. I worked hard throughout my school career and I put in the work every&nbsp;day. I worked hard in class and revised the work at home and worked over weekends and holidays for years,&rdquo; Strydom said.Being a member of his school&rsquo;s student council kept him busy and forced him to manage his time.WATCH: SA's top matric says consistent hard work pays off24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.